2015 Video Game Score of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.geoffknorr.com Official Website of Geoff Knorr]\n* {{IMDb name|3214530}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Knorr, Geoff}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American classical composers]]\n[[Category:Video game composers]]\n[[Category:Peabody Institute alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Geoff Knorr\n| image               =Geoff Knorr 2017.jpg\n| background          = non_performing_personnel\n| birth_name          =\n| alias               =\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1985|6|13|df=y}}\n| death_date          =\n| origin              = [[Framingham]], [[Massachusetts]], [[United States]]\n| genre               = {{flatlist|\n*[[Video game music]]\n*[[Contemporary classical music]]\n}}\n| occupation          = {{flatlist|\n*[[Composer]]\n*[[Audio Engineer]]\n*[[Sound Designer]]\n}}\n| instrument          = \n| years_active        = 2000\u2013present\n| label               = \n| associated_acts     =\n| website             = www.geoffknorr.com\n}}\n\n'''Geoff Knorr''' (born 13 June 1985) is an American composer, orchestrator, and sound designer.  He has worked on video game titles such as ''[[Civilization V]]'', ''[[Civilization: Beyond Earth]]'', ''[[Civilization VI]]'', ''[[Galactic Civilizations III]]'', and ''[[Ashes of the Singularity]]''.   \n\nKnorr was born in [[Framingham, Massachusetts]] and grew up in [[Marietta, Georgia]].  He took piano and cello lessons at a young age and he composed his first piece of music in eighth grade.<ref>Greening, Chris. [http://www.squareenixmusic.com/features/interviews/michaelcurran.shtml \"Interview: The Orchestral Music and Interactive Sounds of Civilization V\"], ''Square Enix Music Online''.</ref> He studied composition with [[Christopher Theofanidis]] and [[Michael Hersch]] and recording arts and sciences at the 